n}$ and $\\Sigma_e$. Therefore, the basic trends\nobserved in the local universe were already established at $z\\sim1.3$, i.e.\nmore massive spheroids are more metal rich, have lower stellar mass density and\ntend to be older than lower-mass galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 6 Jan 2019 18:59:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 8 Jan 2019 19:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 6 Feb 2019 19:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-08"}
