{"id":"1901.01669","submitter":"Masahiro Hasegawa","authors":"Masahiro Hasegawa and Takeo Kato","title":"Geometrical optimization of pumping power under adiabatic parameter\n  driving","comments":"9 pages, 8 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.7566/JPSJ.89.064706","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mes-hall","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Adiabatic pumping is a fundamental concept in the time-dependent transport of\nmesoscopic devices. To maximize pumping performance, i.e., the amount of\npumping per unit time, it is necessary to carefully manage the driving speed,\nwhich should be sufficiently less than the {\\it limited speed}, an upper bound\nof the driving speed below which non-adiabatic effects are negligible. In\ngeneral, the amount of pumping increases as the contour of the driving\nparameter lengthens, however a long contour diminishes the pumping power\nbecause it requires more time per cycle under the limited speed constraint. We\nconsider this trade-off carefully and show that there should exist an optimized\nperiod and contour to maximize the power of adiabatic pumping. We confirm this\nconclusion based on the results of charge pumping using a single-level quantum\ndot.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Jan 2019 05:04:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Jan 2019 06:23:51 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 18 Jul 2019 08:56:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-24"}
